service: Amplify is a fully managed continuous deployment and hosting service for modern web apps.

operations.CreateBranch: Creates a new Branch for an Amplify App.
operations.CreateDomainAssociation: Create a new DomainAssociation on an App
operations.DeleteApp: Delete an existing Amplify App by appId.
operations.DeleteBranch: Deletes a branch for an Amplify App.
operations.DeleteJob: Delete a job, for an Amplify branch, part of Amplify App.
operations.GetApp: Retrieves an existing Amplify App by appId.
operations.GetBranch: Retrieves a branch for an Amplify App.
operations.GetDomainAssociation: Retrieves domain info that corresponds to an appId and domainName.
operations.GetJob: Get a job for a branch, part of an Amplify App.
operations.ListBranches: Lists branches for an Amplify App.
operations.ListJobs: List Jobs for a branch, part of an Amplify App.
operations.StartJob: Starts a new job for a branch, part of an Amplify App.
operations.StopJob: Stop a job that is in progress, for an Amplify branch, part of Amplify App.
operations.UpdateBranch: Updates a branch for an Amplify App.
operations.UpdateDomainAssociation: Create a new DomainAssociation on an App

refs.ListAppsRequest$nextToken: Pagination token. If non-null pagination token is returned in a result, then pass its value in another request to fetch more entries.
refs.ListAppsResult$nextToken: Pagination token. Set to null to start listing Apps from start. If non-null pagination token is returned in a result, then pass its value in here to list more projects.
refs.ListBranchesRequest$nextToken: Pagination token. Set to null to start listing branches from start. If a non-null pagination token is returned in a result, then pass its value in here to list more branches.
refs.ListBranchesResult$nextToken: Pagination token. If non-null pagination token is returned in a result, then pass its value in another request to fetch more entries.
refs.ListDomainAssociationsRequest$nextToken: Pagination token. Set to null to start listing Apps from start. If non-null pagination token is returned in a result, then pass its value in here to list more projects.
refs.ListDomainAssociationsResult$nextToken: Pagination token. If non-null pagination token is returned in a result, then pass its value in another request to fetch more entries.
refs.ListJobsRequest$nextToken: Pagination token. Set to null to start listing steps from start. If a non-null pagination token is returned in a result, then pass its value in here to list more steps.
refs.ListJobsResult$nextToken: Pagination token. If non-null pagination token is returned in a result, then pass its value in another request to fetch more entries.
